Reconciliation = Detect + Compare + Correct

-Detecting early enough
-Correcting safely 

When can it happen
1) Multiple Source of truth
  - Different services have their own DBs
  - Same entity exists in multiple places
2) Async Communication
3) External System 
4) Eventual Consistency Req
5) Retries 
6) Buisness Rules Criticalness 

What can happen
1) Missing data
2) Duplicate data
3) Diverging state
4) Partial completion
5) External mismatch

Detect
1) Event-based detection
    Missing event, Duplicate event, Out-of-order events
2) Time-based detection
    Expected within X time but didn’t happen
3) Trigger-based detection
    Hook into workflows
4) Periodic scanning
    Run jobs to find inconsistencies
5) Constraint violation detection
    Rules broken

Compare
1) Key-based comparison
2) Field-level comparison
3) Checksum / hash comparison
4) Version comparison
5) Event log comparison
6) Aggregate comparison
7) External comparison

Correct
1) Retry
2) Replay
3) Upsert / Patch state
4) Compensation
5) Deduplication
6) Merge
7) Manual intervention



